2481-4 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cPZfXUj5l4sC |ref=Holzer06}} \n*{{cite book |last=Konstam |first=Angus |title=Hampton Roads 1862: First Clash of the Ironclads |ref=Konstam |publisher=Osprey Publishing |year=2002 |isbn=978-1-84176-410-8}} 96 pages.\n*{{cite book |last=Konstam |first=Angus |title=Union Monitor 1861\u201365 |ref=Konstam2 |publisher=Osprey Publishing |isbn=978-1-84176-306-4|date=2002-01-25 }} \n*{{cite book |last=Leckie |first=Robert |title=None Died in Vain: The Saga of the American Civil War |ref=Leckie |publisher=Harper-Collins |location=New York |year=1990 |isbn=978-0-06-016280-1 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/nonediedinvainsa00leck }} \n*{{cite book |last=Maclay |first=Edgar Stanton |title=A history of the United States Navy, from 1775 to 1893 |ref=Maclay |year=1894 |authorlink=Edgar Stanton Maclay |publisher=D. Appleton & Company |location=New York |url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_UHWpn7IEuMoC}} \n*{{cite web |last=Mariners' Museum |url=http://themarinersmuseum.org/uss-monitor-center/naming-monitor |title=The Naming of the Monitor |ref=Mariner |publisher=The Mariner's Museum |location=Newport News, Virginia |accessdate=16 June 2013}}\n*{{cite web |last=Mariners' Museum |url=http://www.marinersmuseum.org/uss-monitor-center/john-payne-bankhead |title=John Payne Bankhead |ref=Mariner2013 |publisher=The Mariner's Museum |location=Newport News, Virginia |accessdate=30 June 2013}}\n*{{cite web |last=Mariners' Museum |url=http://www.marinersmuseum.org/uss-monitor-center/last-voyage-monitor-december-24th-forward |title=Last Voyage of the Monitor: December 24th \u2013 Forward |ref=Mariner24 |publisher=The Mariner's Museum |location=Newport News, Virginia |accessdate=30 June 2013}}\n*{{cite web |title=George S. Geer Papers, 1862\u20131866 |first=George S. |last=Geer |ref=Geer |publisher=The Mariner's Museum, Newport News, Virginia |accessdate=August 15, 2013 |url=http://www.marinersmuseum.org/sites/default/fil