own: The USS Merrimack-CSS Virginia from Construction to Destruction |ref=Park |publisher=Naval Institute Press |location=Annapolis, Maryland |year=2007 |isbn=978-1-59114-659-9}} \n*{{cite book |last=Parkes |first=Oscar |title=British Battleships |ref=Parkes |publisher=Naval Institute Press |location=Annapolis, Maryland |year=1990 |edition=reprint of the 1957 |isbn=978-1-55750-075-5}}\n*{{cite book |last=Quarstein |first=John V. |title=The Battle of the Ironclads |ref=Quarstein99 |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |year=1999 |isbn=978-0-7385-0113-0 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/battleofironclad0000quar }} \n*{{cite book |last=Quarstein |first=John V. |title=A History of Ironclads: The Power of Iron Over Wood |ref=Quarstein06 |publisher=The History Press |year=2006 |isbn=978-1-59629-118-8}} \n*{{cite book |last=Quarstein |first=John V. |title=The Monitor Boys: The Crew of the Union's First Ironclad |ref=Quarstein10 |publisher=The History Press |year=2010 |isbn=978-1-59629-455-4}} \n*{{cite book |last=Quarstein |first=John V. |title=The CSS Virginia: Sink Before Surrender |ref=Quarstein12 |publisher=The History Press |year=2012 |isbn=978-1-60949-580-0}} \n*{{cite book |last=Rawson |first=Edward K. |last2=Woods |first2=Robert H. |title=Official Records of the Union and Confederate Navies in the War of the Rebellion |ref=Rawson |publisher=Government Printing Office, Secretary of the Navy, John D. Long |location=Washington |year=1897}}\n*{{cite book |title=Our Iron-clad Ships: Their Qualities, Performances, and Cost. With Chapters on Turret Ships, Iron-clad Rams |last=Reed |first=Sir Edward James |ref=Reed |location=London |publisher=J. Murray |year=1869 |isbn= |url=https://archive.org/details/ourironcladship01reedgoog}} 332 pages.\n*{{cite book |last=Rhodes |first=James Ford |title=History of the Civil War |ref=Rhodes1917 |publisher=Macmillan & Co.|location=New York, Boston, London |year=1917 |oclc= |url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_T2eM6_ON2HkC}} \n* {{cite book |last=Roberts |first=William H. |title=USS New Ironsides in the Civil War |ref=Roberts99 |year=1999|publisher=Naval Institute Press|location=Annapolis, Maryland|isbn=978-1-55750-695-5}}\n*{{cite book |last=Roberts |first=William H. |location=Baltimore, Maryland |title=Civil War Ironclads: The U.S. Navy and Industrial Mobilization |ref=Roberts02 |publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-8018-8751-2}} \n* {{cite book|last=Silverstone|first=Paul H.|title=Civil War Navies 1855\u20131883|publisher=Routledge|location=New York|year=2006|series=The U.S. Navy Warship Series|isbn=978-0-415-97870-5|ref=Silverstone}}\n*{{cite web |title=American Civil War Issue |url=http://arago.si.edu/index.asp?con=2&cmd=1&id=192338&img=1&mode=1&pg=1&tid=2043413 |accessdate=August 11, 2013 |publisher=Smithsonian National Postal Museum |ref=SNPM}}\n*{{Cite book|last1=Southerland |first1=DG |last2= Davidson | first2=DL |chapter=Electronic diving data collection during Monitor expedition 2001 |ref=Southerland |year=2002 |volume=2 |title=Oceans 2002 |doi=10.1109/OCEANS.2002.1192089 |isbn=978-0-7803-7534-5}}\n*{{cite book |last=Stern |first=Philip Van Doren |title=The Confederate Navy |ref=Stern |publisher=Doubleday & Company |location=New York |year=1962 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=GDeqAAAAIAAJ |lccn=62-15914}} \n*{{cite book |last=Still |first=William N. |editor-last=Hill |editor-first=Dina B.|title=Ironclad Captains: The Commanding Officers of the U. S. S. Monitor |ref=Still88 |publisher=National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, U.S. Government Printing Office |location=Washington, D.C. |year=1988 |isbn=978-0-16-003560-9 |url=http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/CZIC-e595-m7-s74-1988/html/CZIC-e595-m7-s74-1988.htm}} 83 pages.\n*{{cite book |last=Sutherland |first=Jonathan |title=African Americans at War: An Encyclopedia, Volume 1 |year=2004 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |isbn=978-1-57607-746-7}} \n*{{cite journal |last=Thompson |first=Stephen C. |year=199