GKmaHDEC}}\n\n===Primary sources===\n*{{cite book |last=Brooke |ref=Brooke |first=John Mercer |authorlink=John Mercer Brooke |title=Ironclads and Big Guns of the Confederacy: The Journal and Letters of John M. Brooke |publisher=Univ of South Carolina Press |year=2002 |isbn=978-1-57003-418-3}} \n*{{cite book |first=Cornelius Scranton |last=Bushnell |first2=John |last2=Ericsson |first3=Gideon |last3=Welles |ref=Bushnell |title=The original United States warship \"Monitor\" |publisher=National Memorial Association |location=New Haven, Connecticut |year=1899 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FLlAAAAAYAAJ}} \n*{{cite book |last=Dahlgren |first=Madeleine Vinton |title=Memoir of John A. Dahlgren, Rear-admiral United States Navy |ref=Dahlgren |publisher=J. R. Osgood |year=1882 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vfpBAAAAYAAJ}} \n* {{cite web |title=An Eye-Witness Account of the Battle Between the U.S.S. Monitor and the C.S.S. Virginia |year=1862 |last= Green (USN) |first= Lieutenant Samuel Dana |ref=Green |publisher=U.S. Navy, Naval Historical Foundation, Washington, DC |accessdate=18 July 2013 |url=http://www.navyhistory.org/eye-witness-account-battle-between-uss-monitor-css-virginia/}}\n*{{cite book |title=OFFICIAL RECORDS of the UNION AND CONFEDERATE NAVIES in the WAR OF THE REBELLION |last=Rawson |first=Edward K., Superintendent Naval War Records |last2=Woods |first2=Robert H. |ref=Rawson |year=1898 |publisher=Published by [[John Davis Long|John D. Long]], Secretary of the Navy, Government Printing Office |location=Washington D. C. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=96cSAAAAYAAJ}} \n*{{cite book |title=Diary of Gideon Welles, Secretary of the Navy Under Lincoln and Johnson |volume=1 |last=Welles |first=Gideon |authorlink=Gideon Welles |ref=Welles |year=1911 |publisher=Houghton Mifflin Company |location=Boston and New York |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jsdFt7XOr9QC}}\n*{{cite book |title=The Monitor and the Merrimac: Both Sides of the Story |last=Wor