 War in Fifty Objects |ref=Holzer13 |publisher=Penguin Books: New York Historical Society |location=New York |year=2013 }} 416 pages.\n*{{cite book |editor-last=Johnson |editor-first=Robert Underwood |editor-first2=C.C. |editor-last2=Buel |editor-link=Robert Underwood Johnson |title=Battles and Leaders of the Civil War |volume=I |publisher=Century Company |location=New York |year=1887 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Mokin |first=Arthur |title=Ironclad: the Monitor and the Merrimack |authorlink= |publisher=Presidio Press |year=1991 |isbn=978-0-8914-1405-6 |ref=mokin |url=https://archive.org/details/ironcladmonitorm00moki }}\n*{{cite book|last=Peterkin |first=Ernest W.|title=Drawings of the U.S.S. Monitor: A Catalog and Technical Analysis|authorlink= |publisher=National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration |year=1985|isbn=|url=https://archive.org/stream/drawingsofussmon00pete#page/n5/mode/2up}}\n*{{cite book |last=Quarstein |first=John V. |year=2000 |title=C.S.S. Virginia, Mistress of Hampton Roads |ref=Quarstein2k |publisher=self-published for the Virginia Civil War Battles and Leaders Series |isbn=978-1-56190-118-0}}\n* {{cite book |last=Quarstein |first=John V. |ref=Quarstein97 |title= The Civil War on the Virginia Peninsula |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |year=1997 |isbn=978-0-7385-4438-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wSBRAdLN7X4C}}\n*{{cite book |last=Sheridan |first=Robert E. |title=Iron from the Deep: The Discovery and Recovery of the USS Monitor |ref=Sheridan |publisher=Naval Institute Press |location=Annapolis, Maryland |year=2004 |isbn=978-1-55750-413-5 }} \n* {{cite book |last=Snow |first=Richard |title=Iron Dawn: The Monitor, the Merrimack, and the Civil War Sea Battle that Changed History |authorlink= |publisher=Scribner|year=2016 |isbn=978-1-4767-9420-4 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=USGzCwAAQBAJ |ref=snow}}.\n*{{cite book |last=Still |first=William N., Jr. |title=Iron Afloat: The Story of the Confederate Armorclads |isbn=978-0-87249-616-3 |edi